                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Hatchbacks: A Dying Breed in North America's Car Market in 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-unlikely-survival-of-a-niche-market-darling/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Brent vd Schyff]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025_toyota_gr-corolla_premium-plus_at_supersonicred_002-1500x1000.jpg" length="269" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Volkswagen]]></category><category><![CDATA[Toyota]]></category><category><![CDATA[Corolla]]></category><category><![CDATA[Honda]]></category><category><![CDATA[Civic Type R]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mini]]></category><category><![CDATA[John Cooper Works Coupe]]></category><category><![CDATA[BMW]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audi]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mercedes-Benz]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Once a global sensation, hatchbacks are now a rarity. Discover the surprising reasons behind their decline and whether a comeback is coming.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Please excuse the headline (or don't), but sounding the alarm and issuing the public service announcement is needed. Globally, it was a popular choice from the 60s stemming from an international oil crisis, peaking in the 90s in a widespread way, but now, hatchbacks (or rather performance hatchbacks) are all but dead, a figment of what they once were.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 19:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-unlikely-survival-of-a-niche-market-darling/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[7 Linux Distributions I Tested in the Past Year, Ranked]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-distros-i-tried-in-the-past-year-ranked/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/08/a-laptop-panel-with-several-linux-distributions-running-in-terminal-connections-and-virtual-machines.jpg" length="303" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[KDE Plasma]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Which one is missing from this list?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Over the past year I've booted numerous Linux distributions, and seven of them I installed on bare metal and put to the test with daily use. Here are those seven distributions (also called distros) in order of worst to best experience.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 19:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-distros-i-tried-in-the-past-year-ranked/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Korean EV That Feels More Expensive Than It Is]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/korean-ev-feels-more-expensive-than-it-is/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/2025-genesis-gv60-feature.jpg" length="399" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It may cost more than its siblings, but this Korean EV feels way fancier than the price tag suggests.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The clock’s ticking—September 30 is the last day to <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/ev-phev-tax-credit-guide-sept-30/" target="_blank">snag that sweet $7,500 federal tax credit</a> on a new EV. No wonder dealerships are moving metal faster than ever.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/korean-ev-feels-more-expensive-than-it-is/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Touchpad Gestures That Help Me Navigate Windows Faster]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/touchpad-gestures-to-navigate-windows-faster/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/a-person-using-the-laptop-s-touchpad.jpg" length="1668" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Accessibility]]></category><category><![CDATA[customization]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Swipe your way through Windows!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Did you know Windows lets you switch between apps and get around the interface using just the touchpad? This means you don’t always need to reach for the keyboard or mouse, making navigation quicker and more efficient. Let’s dive into how touchpad gestures can help you get things done faster.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 18:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/touchpad-gestures-to-navigate-windows-faster/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 TV Shows That Pick Up Where Their Movies Left Off]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/tv-shows-that-pick-up-where-movies-left-off/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark McPherson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/close-up-of-the-doll-chucky-from-the-tv-series-chucky.jpg" length="225" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            For those who need more after the movie, these TV shows keep going where the films end.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When a movie ends, you sometimes just want more. You want to follow more of the story and characters, enticed to see what happens next. Typically, you’d wait for a sequel, but movie sequels take time to produce, and you’ll likely be waiting years for the next entry.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/tv-shows-that-pick-up-where-movies-left-off/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Love Video Game Developer Commentaries, These Are My Favorites]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-love-video-game-developer-commentaries-these-are-my-favorites/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Maximilian Padilla-Rodriguez]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/developer-commentary.jpg" length="1500" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[BioShock Remastered]]></category><category><![CDATA[Monkey Island 2: LeChuck's Revenge]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deus Ex: Human Revolution Director's Cut]]></category><category><![CDATA[Ghost of Tsushima Director's Cut]]></category><category><![CDATA[games]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There's a story behind every work of art, but these games let you hear it straight from the creators.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>For most games, the stories behind their development are a lot more complicated than you can believe. While most of these stories are only ever discussed behind closed doors, some games unveil their behind-the-scenes secrets through developer commentary.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 17:31:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-love-video-game-developer-commentaries-these-are-my-favorites/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8 Linux User Management Tricks With the usermod Command]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-user-management-tricks-with-the-usermod-command/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Zunaid Ali]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tux-the-linux-mascot-using-a-laptop-in-front-of-cinnamon-desktop-mountains-logo.png" length="1064" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Manage users like a pro.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The usermod command is a tool for updating details about an existing user account in your system. It's kind of like editing the "profile" of a Linux user. With it, you can adjust anything from the username to the login shell, without needing to delete and recreate the account.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-user-management-tricks-with-the-usermod-command/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Top 10 Websites That Defined the Early 2000s Internet]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/top-websites-that-defined-the-early-2000s-internet/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/retro-style-illustration-of-a-2000s-website-with-a-search-bar-digital-2000s-text-and-logos-of-neopets-newgrounds-xanga-and-yahoo-alongside-vintage-web-ads-and-a-pixelated-cursor.png" length="1183" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tech Throwback]]></category><category><![CDATA[internet]]></category><category><![CDATA[Internet Explorer]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The best sites from the Golden Era of the internet.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Back in the time of dial-up internet, the web was a far more colorful and chaotic place. Instead of spending most of our time on a handful of websites like we do now, web surfing was a real and fun activity.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/top-websites-that-defined-the-early-2000s-internet/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Windows Battery Settings That Actually Extended My Laptop’s Battery Life]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/change-windows-battery-settings/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/person-using-a-laptop-with-a-low-battery-icon-and-an-alert.jpg" length="738" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Charge less, do more!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Sick of your laptop battery running out in no time? It’s frustrating—especially when you can’t stay near a power outlet. I used to struggle with this too, but a few tweaks helped my laptop last longer on a single charge. Here are some tweaks you can make to save energy and stay unplugged for longer.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 16:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/change-windows-battery-settings/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[What Is Gaming Mode on a Motherboard, and Should You Enable It?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/my-motherboard-has-a-gaming-mode-heres-why-ive-disabled-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/final.jpg" length="338" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[AMD]]></category><category><![CDATA[CPUs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Gaming PCs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Confusingly, all Game Mode does is reduce performance.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you've recently built or bought an AMD-powered gaming PC and explored its BIOS, you might have noticed an option called "Gaming Mode," "Turbo Mode," or similar. However, this feature isn’t a simple performance boost you'd expect given its name. Here's what it actually does.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 14 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/my-motherboard-has-a-gaming-mode-heres-why-ive-disabled-it/</guid></item></channel>
